author: Wires English | Press Trust of India
title: Man held on charges of attempt to rape daughter
text:
Comments 
Kendrapara (Odisha), Oct 20: A 50-year-old man from a remote village here was arrested today on charges of attempting to rape his 18-year-old daughter. (Also Read: 5-yr-old girl raped by domestic help) 
The police said today that Kiran Nayak, a resident of Chandanpur village under Rajnagar police station, was arrested after his daughter complained to the police that he had made advances to her in a drunken state. 
The girl’s mother also supported the claim of her daughter.”The victim and the accused were first sent for medical examination and later the accused was arrested and remanded to judicial custody,” Sritikantha Kanungo, Inspector of Police, Rajnagar police station, said.
